Justice Minister Sansan Kambile said the government had asked the public prosecutor to bring those involved to justice. He accused the opposition of assault following violent clashes during the election period. The opposition has accused President Alassana Ouattara, who has won a third term in office, of an electoral coup. The European Union and United Nations say they are deeply concerned about escalating tensions in the country, where thousands have fled their homes fearing further unrest. --BBC--